<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-01-12T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-01-06T00:00:00-05:00" n="572" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d572">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 822.00/193.]</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Minister</gloss> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegrams.—Paraphrases.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Quito</hi></placeName>, (<date ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-document-content-and-sibling-dates" calendar="gregorian" notAfter="1912-01-12T23:59:59-05:00" notBefore="1912-01-06T00:00:00-05:00"><hi rend="italic">undated</hi></date>)<hi rend="italic">; received January
                                    12, 1912</hi>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>The January 6 instruction from the Department was complied with
                            immediately.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Young.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
